article.description: Kali Bennett scored 15 points and had 15 rebounds to lead Arizona State (No. 13 ESPN/USA Today, No. 17 AP) to a 65-53 victory over Hawaii on Friday night.
article.headline: Bennett's double-double powers Sun Devils win in Rainbow Wahine Classic
article.linkText: Arizona State rebounds with victory over Hawaii
article.story:
HONOLULU -- Kali Bennett scored 15 points and had 15 rebounds to lead Arizona State (No. 13 ESPN/USA Today, No. 17 AP) to a 65-53 victory over Hawaii on Friday night.

Danielle Orsillo added 15 points for Arizona State (3-1) in the opening game of the Rainbow Wahine Classic.

The Sun Devils controlled the boards, outrebounding Hawaii 46-33, and built a 32-22 halftime lead over the Rainbow Wahine (1-3).

Keisha Kanekoa scored 15 points to lead Hawaii, which lost its third straight after winning coach Dana Takahara-Dias' debut.

The win helped the Sun Devils recover from a loss to Xavier last week that dropped them three spots in the rankings.
